        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-11-20 15:19:56.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1\n\nPls clarify why this change introduced into Casablanca branch?",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "6c6efdd5bfa280e681beb9d61357bf5d2d589b67",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 3081,
          "name": "Jakub Dudycz",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "jakub.dudycz@nokia.com",
          "username": "dudini1"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-11-21 10:21:18.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> Pls clarify why this change introduced into Casablanca branch?\n\nThis is a bugfix. Before we were rejecting requests with common event header's \"sequence\" field equal to 0, which wasn't expected behavior, because this is expected to be a commonly present value in our requests.\n\nDefault value of this field in proto file is 0, therefore we had to remove this field from required fields in our api requests, otherwise it would be impossible to tell if zero-valued sequence was explicitly set to 0, or wasn't set at all.\n\nWe also decided to tighten the validation of vesEventListenerVersion to avoid the cases when it was set to strange values",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "2572d626847323fa2b4ba24577407ed6460c03e2",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 3081,
          "name": "Jakub Dudycz",
